WEBVTT

00:00.086 --> 00:02.928
<i>Previously on AMC's
"Better Call Saul"...</i>

00:02.953 --> 00:05.029
I want a new front.

00:05.054 --> 00:06.765
My father is a simple man.

00:06.790 --> 00:08.613
You will teach him.

00:08.615 --> 00:10.467
[Coughs]

00:10.492 --> 00:12.211
Tonight, I celebrate

00:12.236 --> 00:13.803
with the world's best attorney.

00:13.805 --> 00:14.970
Have you given any thought

00:14.972 --> 00:16.546
to what you're gonna
do for the next year?

00:16.563 --> 00:18.164
I'm out 4,000 bucks.

00:18.189 --> 00:19.689
So you're gonna keep
paying for half a law office

00:19.714 --> 00:21.447
even though you're not practicing law?

00:21.472 --> 00:23.539
I'll hold up my end, you hold up yours.

00:23.564 --> 00:26.171
I'm selling advertising...
why not advertise?

00:26.196 --> 00:27.639
What commercial did you run?

00:27.664 --> 00:28.773
I made a new one.

00:28.798 --> 00:30.208
_

00:30.699 --> 00:34.712
[Footsteps approach]

00:34.737 --> 00:38.026
[Birds chirping]

00:40.176 --> 00:43.544
[Footsteps approach]

00:45.000 --> 00:51.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:52.954 --> 00:54.316
[Slurps]

00:55.557 --> 00:57.757
[Footsteps approach]

00:57.760 --> 00:59.827
[Vehicle door opens, closes]

00:59.829 --> 01:03.163
[Footsteps approach]

01:03.165 --> 01:05.299
[Vehicle door opens, closes]

01:08.170 --> 01:10.304
[Vehicle door opens, closes]

01:14.140 --> 01:16.832
[Vehicle door opens, closes]

01:19.100 --> 01:20.473
[Man clears throat]

01:21.953 --> 01:25.321
[Vehicle approaching]

01:34.797 --> 01:37.831
[Brakes squeal]

01:53.030 --> 01:54.709
[Sniffles] Name?

01:55.055 --> 01:57.451
Um. [Clears throat]
James McGill. [Sniffles]

01:57.491 --> 01:58.890
Bring your card?

01:58.892 --> 02:00.404
Yeah.

02:01.503 --> 02:03.506
[Sighs]

02:07.414 --> 02:09.193
[Clears throat]

02:09.219 --> 02:10.685
Sign there.

02:17.356 --> 02:19.381
[Horn honks in distance]

02:21.326 --> 02:23.192
Can I read it first?

02:23.217 --> 02:24.731
It's just a waiver.

02:24.756 --> 02:27.270
We're not responsible
if you hurt yourself.

02:27.295 --> 02:30.420
[Train whistle blows in distance]

02:32.660 --> 02:34.126
[Sighs]

02:37.831 --> 02:41.199
[Engine rumbling]

02:44.938 --> 02:46.905
[Gearshift clicks, door creaks]

02:46.907 --> 02:48.206
[Engine shuts off]

03:00.639 --> 03:04.007
[Wind whistling]

03:19.936 --> 03:23.304
[Vehicles passing]

03:36.205 --> 03:38.201
[Scoffs]

03:55.031 --> 03:58.399
[Cellphone vibrating]

04:02.837 --> 04:05.450
Good morning. Saul Goodman Productions.

04:07.421 --> 04:08.642
T-that's right.

04:08.667 --> 04:11.623
We, uh... we do it all...
we write it, shoot it,

04:11.625 --> 04:13.510
get ya on the air for
one low, low price.

04:13.535 --> 04:15.768
May I ask what business you have?

04:16.430 --> 04:17.555
Computer repair?

04:17.581 --> 04:20.432
That is a perfect business
to advertise on television

04:20.434 --> 04:23.521
because, you know,
computers are our future.

04:23.546 --> 04:25.179
[Chuckles]

04:26.562 --> 04:27.928
Uh...

04:28.282 --> 04:30.415
yes, well, our rates are...

04:30.440 --> 04:31.946
- [Trucks engines rumbling]
- Ah!

04:33.048 --> 04:35.398
Sorry. That was, uh, one of our trucks.

04:35.423 --> 04:37.545
We're, uh, location shooting today.

04:37.570 --> 04:39.703
It's a big production, actually.

04:39.728 --> 04:43.521
Our usual rate is one
commercial, one airing...

04:43.546 --> 04:45.646
$850, but you're in luck...

04:45.648 --> 04:48.384
today, we have a one-time special.

04:48.409 --> 04:49.657
Our Elite package.

04:49.682 --> 04:52.275
Seven commercials, seven airings

04:52.300 --> 04:54.751
for forty...

04:55.167 --> 04:58.110
forty-six hundred dollars.

04:58.353 --> 05:00.526
Yeah. Forty-six hundred dollars.

05:00.551 --> 05:02.597
And we can a... Hello?

05:03.674 --> 05:05.034
Hello?

05:06.987 --> 05:08.231
[Cellphone beeps]

05:09.599 --> 05:11.832
[Engines rumbling]

05:14.120 --> 05:17.411
No, I didn't, because you
keep putting me on hold.

05:17.413 --> 05:18.913
[Vehicle passing]

05:18.915 --> 05:20.748
Okay, my situ... Hello?

05:20.750 --> 05:22.511
My sit... yes, my situation is this.

05:22.536 --> 05:25.409
I... two months ago,
I paid for a full year,

05:25.434 --> 05:28.155
uh, but, due to
unforeseen circumstances,

05:28.157 --> 05:31.222
I'm not gonna be a lawyer
for the next 12 months.

05:31.247 --> 05:33.360
- [Vehicle passing]
- [Sighs]

05:33.362 --> 05:35.151
Uh-huh. Yes, suspended.

05:35.176 --> 05:37.250
So I'm not practicing,

05:37.275 --> 05:40.093
so I don't need malpractice insurance,

05:40.118 --> 05:43.186
and I'd like to speak to
someone about a refund.

05:44.188 --> 05:47.178
But y... well, then, may
I please speak to someone

05:47.203 --> 05:48.848
who <i> can</i> make a decision?

05:48.873 --> 05:50.978
No, no, no. Don't put
me on hold again, please.

05:50.980 --> 05:53.180
He... Hello? He...

05:53.182 --> 05:55.216
[Vehicle passing]

05:55.218 --> 05:56.851
[Horn honks]

05:59.789 --> 06:02.185
[Whistle blowing]

06:10.339 --> 06:13.575
[Vehicle passing]

06:19.195 --> 06:21.196
Wait a minute. This says 30 minutes.

06:21.221 --> 06:22.655
Yep.

06:22.680 --> 06:24.545
We were out here for four hours.

06:24.547 --> 06:26.347
You were on your phone.

06:26.349 --> 06:28.758
You knew the rules when you signed up.

06:28.783 --> 06:31.250
But I collected more garbage
than anybody out here.

06:31.275 --> 06:33.359
I have to be able to conduct business

06:33.384 --> 06:34.570
to earn a living.

06:34.595 --> 06:36.056
No. [Scoffs]

06:36.058 --> 06:37.930
What do you mean "no"?

06:37.955 --> 06:40.861
Think of community
service as your jail time.

06:40.863 --> 06:42.696
No phones allowed in jail.

06:42.698 --> 06:45.023
W-w-well, hold on there, buddy.

06:45.048 --> 06:47.349
I mean, who do you think you are, huh?

06:47.374 --> 06:50.074
Y-y-you think you can
treat us like this? Yeah?

06:50.099 --> 06:51.469
We're out here for the good

06:51.494 --> 06:54.469
of the great city of
Albuquerque... not for you.

06:54.494 --> 06:55.927
You're not our lord and master.

06:55.952 --> 06:57.722
You don't get to sit back and decide

06:57.747 --> 07:00.281
who's worthy and who isn't.

07:00.283 --> 07:01.766
Am I right?

07:02.781 --> 07:05.367
Dude, are you gonna
get in the van or what?

07:07.819 --> 07:10.453
C'mon. 30 minutes?
That stuff's not right.

07:10.478 --> 07:11.836
You can do better than that.

07:13.326 --> 07:15.947
[Sighs] We could make it zero.

07:20.388 --> 07:22.088
[Sighing]

07:25.074 --> 07:26.891
[Paper rustles]

07:26.916 --> 07:28.853
[Sighs]

07:28.878 --> 07:31.812
[Horn blares]

07:32.725 --> 07:36.736
♪ ♪

07:36.761 --> 07:41.859
